name: fireemblem-cipher-utils
description: Utils to manage Fire Emblem Cipher decks

packageJSON.name: fireemblem-cipher-utils
packageJSON.description: Utils that help managing a collection of Fire Emblem Cipher cards

commit.message: Have basic project set up to begin development

releases.name: 0.9.7 beta
releases.body:
- Added a bunch of missing cards
- Added tons of missing icons (dragon's vein, union skill, bond skill, etc)
- Fixed sort menu

releases.name: 0.9.5 beta
releases.body:
- Added booster box 7 cards
- Removed replicating and syncing of card database, since I have to release a new version now for new cards anyway due to images not being embedded in the db anymore

releases.name: 0.9.4 beta
releases.body:
- Fixed issue where wrong db was being replicated from 

If coming from 9.3 follow this guide to clear the db
- Hit shit + ctrl + I to open the inspector
- go to the application tab, and then indexed db, expand it 
- expand the _pouch_fireemblem-cipher-cards
- Right click on every item under it and click 'clear'
- Hit ctrl + r
- It should now download the correct db with correctly referenced thumbnails.

releases.name: 0.9.3 beta
releases.body:
- Removed all native node modules
- Switched db adapter to pouchdb-browser
- Created tool to serialize old decks and collections to be imported into the app

releases.name: v0.9.0 beta
releases.body:
- Changed Elibe to Divine Weapons
- Removed deck name character limit
- Bundled booster box 5 cards
- Added Linux version

releases.name: v0.8.0 beta
releases.body:
- Added MacOSX build
- Added text to show that a collection had no cards
- Added clear search button to search input
- Fixed issue where controls for adding cards still showed when a deck wasn't selected (closes #4 )
- Fixed issue where searching for card name + title would make card not be able to be found
- Changed wording of 'no decks selected' and made it to where, when clicked on, it takes you to manage decks screen
- Reduced the size of Windows installer

releases.name: v0.7.0 beta
releases.body:
- Added collection management
- Added ability to page through cards when looking a specific card in context (can also use left and right arrow keys)
- Added FAQ section
- Improved ability to change the number of cards in a deck
- Improved ReadMe
- Fixed issues where skill names would have tokens replaced with icons
- Fixed issue where app would lock up if a card didn't have proper affinities

releases.name: v0.6.0 beta
releases.body:
- Added sorting for cards
- Added filtering by affinity and set for cards
- Added syncing to a remote server
- Added incrementing/decrementing cards in deck with +/- keys on card detail
- Fixed various issues with skill parsing and missing icons
- Fixed situations where card id's would cause the card to not be able to be viewed

releases.name: v0.5.0 beta
releases.body:
### Good Enough for Beta Build

If updating from v0.4.0 alpha, make sure you export your decks first, or you'll lose them!
- Improved skill parser
- Fixed issue where deck DB was lost on update
- Fixed issue that could happen when trying to set a deleted deck
- Fixed issue where processes would keep being created when trying to print a deck
- Added ability to select a main character for a deck
- Added tooltips for card description
- Added back button to card description
- Removed many dev options from settings menu
- Removed ability to set user images for cards (for now)

releases.name: v0.4.0 alpha
releases.body:
- Added maximize/unmaximize button
- Removed edit pencils in favor of 'edit current deck'
- Added automated testing framework
- Add confirmation for deck deletion
- Allow main character to be set for decks
- Changed text raster icons to svgs
- Made sure placeholders appear when cards don't have images

releases.name: v0.3.0 alpha
releases.body:
- Implemented infinite scrolling for card search
- Added initial card search card loading indicator

releases.name: v0.2.0 alpha
releases.body:
- Implemented auto update flow
- Show version in settings

releases.name: v0.1.0 alpha
releases.body: First release to get the ball rolling on implementing auto updating.
